{"title_page": "Sweet Silence Studios", "text_new": "{{notability|Companies|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Sweet Silence Studios''' was a recording studio originally built by Danish engineers Freddy Hansson, [[Stig Kreutzfeldt]], and [[Flemming Rasmussen]] in February 1976. A variety of artists have recorded there, including [[Cat Stevens]], [[Gasolin]], [[Lone Star (album)|Lone Star]], Ole Prehm, [[Metallica]], [[Sin-Decade|Pretty Maids]], [[C.V. J\u00f8rgensen]] and [[Klich\u00e9]]. The studios closed in 2009, being demolished to make way for an apartment complex and a car park.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/may11/articles/classic-tracks-0511.htm|title=Metallica 'One': Classic Tracks|journal=[[Sound on Sound]]|publisher=SOS Publications Group|date=May 2011|last=Buskin|first=Richard |accessdate=18 January 2013|oclc=61313197}}</ref> Rasmussen then moved to Winding Road Studios in Copenhagen.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{coord missing|Denmark}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Recording studios in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1976]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures demolished in 2009]]\n[[Category:1976 establishments in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Culture in Copenhagen]]\n\n\n{{Denmark-struct-stub}}\n{{Recording-studio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{notability|Companies|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n'''Sweet Silence Studios''' was a recording studio originally built by Danish engineers Freddy Hansson, [[Stig Kreutzfeldt]], and [[Flemming Rasmussen]] in February 1976. A variety of artists have recorded there, including [[Cat Stevens]], [[Gasolin]], [[Lone Star (album)|Lone Star]], Ole Prehm, [[Metallica]], [[Sin-Decade|Pretty Maids]], [[C.V. J\u00f8rgensen]] and [[Klich\u00e9]]. The studios closed in 2009, being demolished to make way for an apartment complex and a car park.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/may11/articles/classic-tracks-0511.htm|title=Metallica 'One': Classic Tracks|journal=[[Sound on Sound]]|publisher=SOS Publications Group|date=May 2011|last=Buskin|first=Richard |accessdate=18 January 2013|oclc=61313197}}</ref> Rasmussen then moved to Winding Road Studios in Copenhagen.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{coord missing|Denmark}}\n\n[[Category:Recording studios in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1976]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures demolished in 2009]]\n[[Category:1976 establishments in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Culture in Copenhagen]]\n\n\n{{Denmark-struct-stub}}\n{{Recording-studio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "Update date format tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sweet_Silence_Studios"}
